<br>
Lord Nagafen fell today to an onslaught of 5 full groups.  It required a second attempt to bring the foul beast down.<br>
<br>
I would like to give special thanks to Clan Autumnwood for sending us reinforcements and more aid to speed along the buffline.<br>
<br>
Extra special thanks to Sefa of Clan Autumnwood who was present the whole time assisting with rezzes and heals.  I wish you the best of luck with your Ragefire camp!<br>
<br>
Our very own Cyanora Mindtrick was also present for buffline, helping the raid along.  Thanks to you, Sister.<br>
<br>
It seems that in everything I do, I have thanks to give to Clan Battle Axe for their staunch support, their sense of honour, and their steadfast friendship.  Special thanks this evening to Dararu Swordfalcon, who's steadfastness helped with the entire process.<br>
<br>
Xelaszan Holyrider and Crombattleaxe the Earth Keeper were not present for the final slaying.  That said, following is the tale of the dragon's hoard which we won:<br>
<br>
Cloak of Flames:  Pacifist Menthu &lt;Vivix Protectorate&gt;<br>
Selo's Drums of the March:  Temperance Descant &lt;Noble Heart&gt;<br>
Selo's Drums of the March:  Randomed for Greed, No one needed it<br>
Gold Plated Koshigatana:  Lorce Dehorse &lt;Forgotten Guard&gt;<br>
Gold Plated Koshigatana:  Thaile Sevenwinters &lt;Paradox Rising&gt;<br>
<br>
Congratulations to all the winners of the rolls this evening!  My thanks to all of you who attended this event, in spite of the admittedly unorthodox loot rules.  I know in my heart that those who came did so with understanding of the principles of friendship and chivalry which inspired those rules.  Thank you for showing me and all of Erollisi Marr that people of your character do indeed walk this virtual world with us.<br>
<br>
I applaud and thank you all.<br>
<br>
I look forward to fighting beside you again!<br>
<br>
Until then, may Quellious grant you serenity.<br>
Theo<br>
<br>
