My Fellow Norrathians,<br>
<br>
I am about to embark on a campaign on Lord Nagafen as RL allows.  This will undoubtedly translate to not being a consistent weekly effort, but I shall put forth my best endeavour as I am able.<br>
<br>
The criteria for being selected for this raid are as follows:<br>
<br>
1.)  Members of Vivix Protectorate and Clan Battle Axe.  These are my brothers, sisters, friends, and sworn allies.  They are first in my thought and heart, and are proven team players.<br>
<br>
2.)  Level and Class.  You must be level 45 minimum to attend this raid.  Special dispensations may be given to bards with good drums.  Critical classes will be selected first, before opening up to reinforced strength.<br>
<br>
3.)  Prior experience and references.  If you are known to us, and are spoken well of by VP or CBA, this will increase your standing.<br>
<br>
4.)  Attitude.  If this is our first meeting, and we hit it off well, you will stand a good chance of being selected.<br>
<br>
5.)  Equipment.  Yes, I list this one last.  Assuming that you are a great person, a reliable teamplayer, well referred, at the end is your MR and FR stats.<br>
<br>
<br>
I am a huge proponent of raids as team events.  A solid team player will always be preferred over the non-teamplayer with 1,000,000pp in gear.<br>
<br>
<br>
That said, I must put forth some guidelines.<br>
<br>
a.)  Lack of team synergy will result in the end of the raid.  I absolutely WILL NOT lead 30 people to their death, even if your 60 High Priest main character is sitting in Buff Hall with a rez stick.<br>
<br>
b.)  A raider who receives more than 2 blemishing notes will be dismissed from the raid.  Should I receive tells from two different people of whining or minor disobedience, you will be dismissed from the raid.  No hard feelings, I understand that we all have bad days.<br>
<br>
c.)  A raider whose gross disobedience results in the death of a fellow raider or who is caught ninjalooting will be soulmarked in my Palm Pilot for posterity.  If you kill someone by accident, I believe you.  If you kill someone in gross defiance, it is no accident.  Ninjalooting is no accident either.<br>
<br>
d.)  Perjury will be soulmarked in my Palm Pilot and put on a Post-It on the top of my monitor for posterity.  If your FR sucks, please say so.  If it is your first time on a dragon raid, please say so.  It's not the end of the world.  It will not affect my opinion of your character.  And it will not automatically mean that you can't come.  Everyone gets one chance to lie to me.  Make it count.<br>
<br>
e.)  Lack of critical mass will result in the end of the raid.  If in my estimation, the raid lacks the strength to accomplish the objective, the raid will be called off.  Feel free to send tells to all your friends and continue.  But once more, I will not lead 30 people to their death and waste their evening if I see that it can be avoided.<br>
<br>
f.)  If you are a great teamplayer and you obviously enjoyed yourself, you will likely be preferred to come with us again.  A friend made is a friend remembered, and I will not forget you.  Don't feel bad if you didn't win the roll today, when I do this again you will get another chance.<br>
<br>
<br>
Loot rules are as follows:<br>
<br>
Red Dragon Scale:  First scale is reserved for Volam Songweaver (if she is present).  Others will be randomed to BRD and WAR level 49+.  Again, if you are under this level don't be afraid to come.  When your time comes, you will get your shot.<br>
<br>
Paladin Book:  First drop is reserved for Xelaszan Holyrider (if he is present).  Others will be randomed to PAL level 49+.<br>
<br>
Cloak of Flames:  First drop is reserved for Crombattleaxe the Earth Keeper (if he is present).  Others will be randomed to WAR, PAL, RNG, SHD, MNK, ROG regardless of level.<br>
<br>
Gauntlets of Fiery Might:  Randomed to MNK and ROG regardless of level.<br>
<br>
Treasure Hunter's Satchel:  Randomed to MNK regardless of level.<br>
<br>
All other items:  Randomed to usable classes regardless of level.<br>
<br>
<br>
I plan to continue this campaign on a spawn-by-spawn basis as RL permits.  I look forward to some exciting and rewarding raids enjoyed by all.  Please do sign up, and bring your grandest sense of adventure and camaraderie!<br>
<br>
